        "### 2) In your own words, summarize the difference between Bayesian and Frequentist statistics\n",
        "\n",
        "If you're unsure where to start, check out [this blog post of Bayes theorem with Python](https://dataconomy.com/2015/02/introduction-to-bayes-theorem-with-python/)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "AADlIVfgDztY",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "Bayesian statistics take a prior probability and update it with new information until it reaches the true value.\n",
        "\n",
        "Frequentist statistics estimate the population value using a sample of the population. The bigger the sample size the better."
      ]
    },
    {
